Texas Air Corp's Continental Airlinesand Eastern Air Lines said they will combine their frequentflyer programs in late April.    Frequent flyer members will begin receiving one monthlystatement that reflects combined earnings from both Continentaland Eastern, the companies said.    Continental said reciprocity between the two programs wasestablished in June 1986 and allowed members of either programto earn miles and redeem points for rewards from the othercarrier. Reuter&#3;